  "prompt": "What is the male version of a mistress?",
  "response": "The term \"mistress\" typically refers to a woman who is romantically or sexually involved with a man, especially one who is married to someone else. The male equivalent of a mistress can be referred to as a \"lover,\" \"paramour,\" or less commonly \"mister.\" However, none of these terms carry exactly the same connotation as \"mistress,\" which often implies an ongoing, secretive, or extramarital relationship. The context in which the term is used often influences the choice of the male counterpart.",
